/-!
# Cameron Ch.3 §3.9 — Distance-transitive graphs

**Theorem 3.17** (Biggs–Smith). Exactly 12 finite distance-transitive
graphs of valency 3 up to isomorphism.

**Theorem 3.18** (Tutte 1947). A finite connected graph of valency 3
whose automorphism group acts transitively on vertices AND edges has
vertex stabiliser of order `3 · 2^a` with `a ≤ 4`.

**Theorem 3.19** (Smith). A finite distance-transitive graph of valency
`> 2` with imprimitive automorphism group is bipartite or antipodal.

These are tangential to Moore57. [skeleton]
-/

namespace Moore57.Papers.CameronCh3

